ter January 1st  2016 and the school code is 003753 by the Priority Deadline   March 1  for incoming cadets April 1   for returning cadets If you miss the Priority Deadline  you should still complete the FAFSA and financial aid application  however the availability of funds will be limited  3  Verification Worksheet Prospective cadets and returning cadets may be selected by the Department of Education for verification  To complete verification  you must provide a completed and signed verification worksheet and also request a copy of the tax return transcript for all tax filers from the IRS  4  Request your transcript here  https www irs gov Individuals Get Transcript   Note  Instead of ordering an IRS tax return transcript you may opt to transfer tax information into your FAFSA by using the Data Retrieval Tool at https studentaid ed gov sa resources irs drt text VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 